Service Level Agreements (SLAs) define the expected uptime and availability of Azure services. They are expressed as a percentage, such as 99.9% uptime.

Higher SLA percentages indicate better reliability.

For example:

* 99.9% uptime allows ~43 minutes of downtime per month
* 99.99% uptime allows ~4 minutes of downtime per month

A real-life use case is selecting services for critical applications. A banking system may require services with high SLAs to ensure minimal downtime.

Another example is designing applications across availability zones to achieve higher SLAs.

Understanding SLAs helps in designing reliable cloud solutions.
